<section xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" id=3D"doc_center_content" i=
temprop=3D"content" lang=3D"en" data-language=3D"en" data-bs-spy=3D"scroll"=
 data-bs-target=3D"#nav_scrollspy"><div id=3D"pgtype-topic">
<section itemprop=3D"content"><h1 class=3D"r2023b" itemprop=3D"title conten=
t" id=3D"example-ex02454996">Register Multimodal 3-D Medical Images</h1><di=
v class=3D"examples_short_list hidden_ios_android"><div data-pane=3D"metada=
ta" class=3D"panel metadata_container panel-default"><div class=3D"panel-bo=
dy metadata_content open_example_div"><button type=3D"button" class=3D"btn =
companion_btn btn_color_blue btn-block copy_cmd_btn" data-toggle=3D"popover=
" data-placement=3D"bottom" data-trigger=3D"hover focus" title=3D"" data-ht=
ml=3D"true" data-content=3D"<code>openExample('images/VolumeRegistrationExa=
mple')</code>" data-original-title=3D"MATLAB Command"><span class=3D"icon-m=
w-copy"><span class=3D"sr-only">Copy Code</span></span>&nbsp; Copy Command<=
/button></div></div></div><div itemscope=3D"" itemtype=3D"http://www.mathwo=
rks.com/help/schema/MathWorksDocPage/Example" itemprop=3D"example" class=3D=
"em_example"><meta itemprop=3D"exampleid" content=3D"images-VolumeRegistrat=
ionExample"><meta itemprop=3D"exampletitle" content=3D"Register Multimodal =
3D Medical Images"></div><span id=3D"VolumeRegistrationExample" class=3D"an=
chor_target"></span><p class=3D"shortdesc">This example shows how to automa=
tically align two volumetric images using intensity-based registration. In =
this example, you register multimodal images acquired using magnetic resona=
nce imaging (MRI) and computed tomography (CT). Multimodal images can be mi=
saligned due to differences in patient positioning (translation or rotation=
) and pixel size (scaling).</p><p>In image registration, there is a <span c=
lass=3D"emphasis"><em>fixed image</em></span> and a <span class=3D"emphasis=
"><em>moving image</em></span>. The position of the fixed image does not ch=
ange. A geometric transformation is applied to the moving image to align it=
 with the fixed image. <span class=3D"emphasis"><em>Intensity-based</em></s=
pan> image registration techniques use information about the pixel intensit=
ies to calculate the geometric transformation. Intensity-based registration=
 is often appropriate for medical images and remote sensing images. To lear=
n more about alternative registration techniques, such as feature-based and=
 control point registration, see <a href=3D"https://ww2.mathworks.cn/help/r=
eleases/R2023b/images/approaches-to-registering-images.html" data-docid=3D"=
images_ug#bvnu5qr" class=3D"a">Choose Image Registration Technique</a>. Thi=
s example uses two intensity-based approaches for 3-D image registration:</=
p><div class=3D"itemizedlist"><ul><li><p>Register the images directly using=
 <a href=3D"https://ww2.mathworks.cn/help/releases/R2023b/images/ref/imregi=
ster.html" data-docid=3D"images_ref#btcaexy-1" class=3D"a"><code class=3D"o=
link">imregister</code></a>.</p></li><li><p>Estimate the geometric transfor=
mation required to map the moving image to the fixed image using <a href=3D=
"https://ww2.mathworks.cn/help/releases/R2023b/images/ref/imregtform.html" =
data-docid=3D"images_ref#btskbz9-1" class=3D"a"><code class=3D"olink">imreg=
tform</code></a>, then apply the transformation using <a href=3D"https://ww=
2.mathworks.cn/help/releases/R2023b/images/ref/imwarp.html" data-docid=3D"i=
mages_ref#btqog63-1" class=3D"a"><code class=3D"olink">imwarp</code></a>.</=
p></li></ul></div><p>Medical Imaging Toolbox=E2=84=A2 provides objects and =
functions that simplify this workflow to automatically manage spatial refer=
encing in the patient coordinate system. To get started, see <a href=3D"htt=
ps://ww2.mathworks.cn/help/releases/R2023b/medical-imaging/ug/medical-image=
-registration.html" data-docid=3D"medical_ug#mw_8948342e-f949-4844-a5bb-b90=
540221748" class=3D"a">Medical Image Registration</a><span role=3D"cross_pr=
od"> (Medical Imaging Toolbox)</span>.</p><div class=3D"procedure"><h3 clas=
s=3D"title" id=3D"VolumeRegistrationExample-1">Load Images</h3><p>This exam=
ple uses a CT image and a T1 weighted MRI image collected from the same pat=
ient. The 3-D CT and MRI data sets are from <a href=3D"https://rire.insight=
-journal.org/download.html" target=3D"_blank">The Retrospective Image Regis=
tration Evaluation (RIRE) Dataset</a>, provided by Dr. Michael Fitzpatrick.=
 For more information, see the <a href=3D"https://rire.insight-journal.org/=
index.html" target=3D"_blank">RIRE Project homepage</a>.</p><p>In this exam=
ple, the MRI scan is the fixed image and the CT image is the moving image. =
The images are stored in the file formats used by the RIRE Project. Use the=
 <code class=3D"literal">helperReadHeaderRIRE</code> helper function to obt=
ain the metadata associated with each image. The helper function is attache=
d to this example as a supporting file.</p><div class=3D"code_responsive -h=
as_code_copy"><div class=3D"programlisting"><div class=3D"codeinput"><div c=
lass=3D"btn-group code_actions"> <button type=3D"button" class=3D"btn btn-d=
efault dropdown-toggle" data-toggle=3D"dropdown" aria-haspopup=3D"true" ari=
a-expanded=3D"false"> <span class=3D"copy_code_popover_target" id=3D"copy_p=
opover_00"><span class=3D"icon-copy" id=3D"copy_popover_00"></span> Get <sp=
an class=3D"caret" id=3D"copy_popover_00"></span></span></button><ul class=
=3D"dropdown-menu dropdown-menu-right copy_code"><li class=3D"copy_code_blo=
ck"><button id=3D"copyBlock00"><span class=3D"icon-copy"></span> Copy Code =
Block</button></li><li role=3D"separator" aria-hidden=3D"true" class=3D"div=
ider"></li><li class=3D"copy_code_openexample"><p><span class=3D"icon-webin=
ar"></span> Copy openExample Command<br><small>Paste command in MATLAB to d=
ownload and open example files</small></p><div role=3D"presentation" class=
=3D"input-group"><input type=3D"text" class=3D"form-control" readonly=3D"" =
value=3D"openExample('images/VolumeRegistrationExample')"><span class=3D"in=
put-group-btn"><button class=3D"btn btn_color_blue" type=3D"button" id=3D"c=
opyCommand00"><span class=3D"icon-copy"><span class=3D"sr-only">Copy</span>=
</span></button></span></div></li></ul></div><pre>fixedHeader =3D helperRea=
dHeaderRIRE(<span style=3D"color:#A020F0">"rirePatient007MRT1.header"</span=
>);
movingHeader =3D helperReadHeaderRIRE(<span style=3D"color:#A020F0">"rirePa=
tient007CT.header"</span>);</pre></div></div></div><p>Use <code class=3D"li=
teral">multibandread</code> to read the binary files that contain the image=
 data.</p><div class=3D"code_responsive -has_code_copy"><div class=3D"progr=
amlisting"><div class=3D"codeinput"><div class=3D"btn-group code_actions"> =
<button type=3D"button" class=3D"btn btn-default dropdown-toggle" data-togg=
le=3D"dropdown" aria-haspopup=3D"true" aria-expanded=3D"false"> <span class=
